wikipedia_page.main: William Collins (died 1859) was a British Whig politicianCollins was elected a Whig Member of Parliament for Warwick at a by-election in 1837—caused by the succession of Charles Canning to the peerage—and held the seat until 1852 when he did not seek re-election.
